<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Assassin Classes <br>
<br>
We know that many players of Camelot are devoted to the Assassin classes of the game (Infiltrator, Shadowblade, Nightshade). Camelot launched with the classes implemented, but not fully effective. Since release, we've added a lot to these classes, including the addition of Safe Fall, redoing combat styles so that these classes do more damage than they used to, and tuning up the way that envenoming weapons (and poison damage) works. We know we're not done with the class - we have a couple of high level skills to add, and there's always tuning and tweaking to be done. However, the proliferation of high level assassin classes shows that the classes are now viable. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
My favorite is that last sentance.  I wonder what the percentages is... and what they consider high level.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 5:01:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How close to viable are we?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I agree with Andorian. If someone thinks assassins are strong in RvR, I wish they would give me a few tips on how to be effective in RvR. I must be missing something so far.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I must be missing something as well(besides more levels). I just dont see how a nightshade is useful unless they are of high level. I spent about 3 hours battling out last night. I 'tried' to fullfill my roles as archer/caster killer:<br>
<br>
Archers:<br>
Now that the arrow gives the direction they shoot from, most archers got rushed by our melees as soon as they shot and werent alone. Or many archers would sit back in a group and fire away. So if I wanted to take out the archer... it would be a kamikaze run. <br>
<br>
Casters:<br>
Most casters run to the front line.. cast and run back. Trying to get behind enemy lines was a dangerous option at my level. Cuz if I died, odds are no one would be able to rez me. So I tried to anticipate the casters that ran to the front line... if I didnt die waiting for one to run up... it was again normally a suicide mission. Once I revealed myself a tank close by would whack me once and I'd die. Or often I would get caught in the AE madness that ensues on the front line. <br>
<br>
<br>
Just seems unless Im high level, Im not very viable in RvR. And I realize thats the case for a lot of the melee classes.  I say a grey Theurgist running up.. casting some sort of mez/root spell and freezing a whole area of us. Here was a sub 20 character making an impact on RvR. Kind of the same for casters who can heal, mes, rez, cast dmg buffs, cast blade turn. <br>
<br>
Seemed the only good I did last night was teach the druids where their rez key was. <p><b>Xumten, Assassin<br>
Winden Drake,  Champion<br>
Brehon of Cair Vie - Percival</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeldirskirnir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keldir Skirnir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 5:14:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How close to viable are we?</span><hr size=1> I kick arse on low level casters, and some archers.  The fighters are no good because they dont die real fast and pop me out of stealth.  I have noticed that the larger percentage of hp you take off a target, the less likely you are to pop out of stealth on a critical.  I can sneak in and one shot grey, green, and sometimes blue casters without appearing, which puzzles a lot of people that are there at the moment.  But thats not a big accomplishment.  A skald could run in and nail a grey caster. <p>Solvarn Astyrnax<br>
